sections.Quotes:
'''Spoken by Jon'''
{{Quote|I never met my mother. My [[Eddard Stark|father]] wouldn't even tell me her name. I don't know if she's living or dead. I don't know if she's a noblewoman or a fisherman's wife or a whore...|[[Jon Snow]] to [[Samwell Tarly]]|Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things}}
{{Quote|I'm the watcher on The Wall.|'''Jon Snow''' taking the black|The Pointy End}}
{{Quote|My father told me big men fall just as quick as little ones, if you put a sword through their hearts.|'''Jon Snow''' to [[Tormund]]|Valar Dohaeris}}
{{Quote|With me, lads. [[Castle Black]]'s not falling tonight.|'''Jon Snow''' during [[Battle of Castle Black|the battle for Castle Black]]|The Watchers on the Wall}}
'''Spoken about Jon'''
{{Quote|A bastard boy with nothing to inherit, off to join the ancient order of the [[Night's Watch]]. Alongside his valiant brothers in arms...|[[Tyrion Lannister]] to '''Jon Snow'''|The Kingsroad}}
{{Quote|Honor made you leave, and honor brought you back.|[[Jeor Mormont]] to '''Jon Snow'''|Fire and Blood}}
{{Quote|Your death will be a gift for them south of [[the Wall]]. They'll never know what you've done. They'll never know how you died. They won't even know your damn name. But they'll be alive because some nameless bastard north of the Wall gave his life for theirs...|[[Qhorin|Qhorin Halfhand]] to '''Jon Snow'''|The Old Gods and the New}}
'''Conversations'''
{{Dialogue a-b-a|Eddard Stark|There's great honor serving in the Night's Watch. The [[House Stark|Starks]] have manned the wall for thousands of years, and you are a Stark. You may not have my name, but you have my blood.|Jon Snow|Is my mother alive? Does she know about me? Where I am, where I'm going? Does she care?|The next time we see each other, we'll talk about your mother. I promise.|[[Eddard Stark|Eddard Stark's]] final words to '''Jon Snow'''|The Kingsroad}}

